      "text": [
        " : «يُكْرَهُ لِلْمُحْرِمِ أَنْ يَجُوزَ ثَوْبُهُ أَنْفَهُ مِنْ أَسْفَلَ» وَ قَالَ «اِضْحَ لِمَنْ أَحْرَمْتَ لَهُ»."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2681 - Hafs ibn al-Bakhtari and Hisham ibn al-Hakam narrated from Abu Abdullah (as) that he said: \"It is disliked for the person in ihram to let their garment cover their nose from below.\"\nImam (as) also said, \"Show openness to the One for whom you have entered the state of ihram.\""
        ]
      }
